# ╔══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╗
# ║  meal-prep environment configuration                           ║
# ║                                                                ║
# ║  There are TWO places env vars live:                           ║
# ║    1. This file (.env.local) — for the TanStack Start app      ║
# ║    2. Convex dashboard / CLI — for the Convex backend          ║
# ║                                                                ║
# ║  See "Convex env vars" section below for what to set there.    ║
# ╚══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════════╝

# ── 1. App-side (.env.local / Vercel dashboard) ─────────────────
# These are read by the TanStack Start server and client.

# Convex deployment identifier (from `npx convex dev` or `npx convex deploy`)
CONVEX_DEPLOYMENT=dev:your-deployment-name

# Convex cloud URL — used by both client (React) and server (auth proxy)
VITE_CONVEX_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.cloud

# Convex HTTP endpoint — used by the auth proxy to forward requests
CONVEX_SITE_URL=https://your-deployment.convex.site

# OpenAI — used by /api/ai/* routes for meal & prep generation
OPENAI_API_KEY=sk-...

# ── 2. Convex-side (set via `npx convex env set KEY value`) ─────
# These are read by Convex server functions (convex/auth.ts).
# They are NOT in this file — set them via CLI or Convex dashboard.
#
#   SITE_URL             = http://localhost:3000          (dev)
#                        = https://your-app.vercel.app    (prod)
#                        → Used as Better Auth baseURL + trustedOrigins.
#                          This is your APP url, not the Convex url.
#
#   BETTER_AUTH_SECRET   = <random 64-char hex string>
#                        → `openssl rand -hex 32` to generate.
#
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID     = <from Google Cloud Console>
#   GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET = <from Google Cloud Console>
#                        → OAuth redirect URI must match SITE_URL:
#                          {SITE_URL}/api/auth/callback/google
